The '''House of Assembly''' was the [[legislature]] of the [[Colony of Jamaica|British colony of Jamaica]].<ref name="PJP">{{cite web | url=http://www.japarliament.gov.jm/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=6&Itemid=23 | title=History of Jamaica's Legislature | publisher=Parliament of Jamaica | accessdate=4 November 2014}}</ref> It held its first meeting on 20 January 1664 at [[Spanish Town]]. For many years, the House of Assembly was dominated by the [[White Jamaican]] [[planter class]]. A law passed in 1840 allowed most blacks and mixed-race men to vote in elections to the Assembly, though the planters continued to dominate it.<ref name="CST">{{cite web | url=http://countrystudies.us/caribbean-islands/19.htm | title=History of Jamaica | work=[[Library of Congress Country Studies]] | publisher=Library of Congress | accessdate=4 November 2014}}</ref> As a result of the [[Morant Bay Rebellion]], the Assembly voted to abolish self-governance in 1865. Jamaica then became a direct-ruled [[crown colony]].
