She was the co-recipient of the [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police|RCMP]]'s Child Recovery Award in 2011.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Forberg, Sigrid |url=http://publications.gc.ca/collections/collection_2012/grc-rcmp/JS62-126-73-2-eng.pdf |title=Finding missing children with Facebook|page=11|journal=Gazette|volume=73|issue=2|year=2011}}</ref> Aftab was the organizer for a 2015 anti-cyberbullying event in Ireland,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/ireland/experts-to-draft-plan-on-online-bullying-327136.html|title=Experts to draft plan on online bullying|publisher=Irish Examiner|date=April 27, 2015|author=Danaher, Dan }}</ref> and has been a member of the advisory boards for [[MTV]]'s A Thin Line,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athinline.org/about|title=About Us: A THIN LINE, MTV’s sexting, cyberbullying, digital dating abuse campaign : www.athinline.org|publisher=|accessdate=December 23, 2015}}</ref> Fair Play, [[Sesame Street]] Online and the [[Ad Council]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/Research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=12035893&privcapId=108192338&previousCapId=108192338&previousTitle=WiredTrust|title=Parry Aftab: Executive Profile & Biography |work=Businessweek.com|accessdate=December 23, 2015}}</ref> Her clients have included [[Facebook]], [[Disney]] and [[Nickelodeon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edtechreview.in/voices/interviews/874-cyberlaw-education-profiled-with-parry-aftab|title=Cyberlaw & Education Profiled with Parry Aftab|author=Berger, Rod |work=EdTechReview|date=December 24, 2013}}</ref> She has been quoted in more than 1500 news and magazine articles and has testified many times before US Congress and the Canadian Parliament on digital policy issues.
